text = "LunCo is an open-source platform for collaborative designing and simulating space missions.

[b]Quick Start Guide:[/b]

[u]Creating and Controlling:[/u]
• [b]Create entities:[/b] Press Alt + [1-5]
• [b]Control entities:[/b] Click on entity buttons at the bottom of screen
• [b]Release control:[/b] Press Backspace key
• [b]Navigate:[/b] Use WASD keys for movement

[u]Camera Controls:[/u]
• [b]Rotate camera:[/b] Right mouse button (RMB) or Arrow keys
• [b]Zoom:[/b] Mouse wheel or +/- keys
• [b]Switch camera:[/b] Press C key to cycle through available cameras
• [b]Reset view:[/b] Press Home key

[u]Resource Network Inspection:[/u]
• [b]View resources:[/b] Select a spacecraft to see floating resource graph
• [b]Toggle floating display:[/b] Press G key
• [b]Detailed inspection:[/b] Press Shift+G for fullscreen view
• [b]Close fullscreen:[/b] Press Esc key

[u]Telemetry & OpenMCT:[/u]
• [b]OpenMCT Dashboard:[/b] Access NASA's OpenMCT for real-time telemetry monitoring
• [b]Access:[/b] Use the menu button or visit [url]https://alpha.lunco.space/mcc/index.html[/url]
• [b]Features:[/b] View position, velocity, and system state in real-time plots

[u]Command Dashboard:[/u]
• [b]Visual Dashboard:[/b] Press [b]F10[/b] to browse and execute commands with interactive parameters (sliders, dropdowns)
• [b]Windowed Mode:[/b] Detach the dashboard into a separate OS window for multi-monitor setups
• [b]Sync:[/b] Commands executed here are also available via OpenMCT

[u]Interface:[/u]
• [b]Menu:[/b] Press Esc key
• [b]Console:[/b] Press ` (backtick) key
• [b]Create NFT sphere:[/b] Hold Ctrl and click on terrain

Explore the lunar surface, collaborate with other users, and help engineer the future of space exploration!"
